track_notes: From Trout Fishery parking lot, take Cat Gap loop trail. At Cat Gap, proceed SW to S andy Gap. Be on the lookout for the spur trail (right) to ascend to the summit.
8.1 mile hike with 2560 EG and EL using the full Cat Gap Loop trail and heading both north and south for a double-header of W4C/CM-094 - Chestnut Knob and W4C/CM-081 - Cedar Rock Mtn.
track_title: Cat Gap Loop with Cedar Rock Mtn and Chestnut Knob

track_notes:
I took FS 471 and parked on Charlies Creek Road at the gate for FS 471D and hiked to the intersection of the Art Loeb Trail.  Turned right on ALT to Butter Gap. I took an unmarked trail straight ahead as my FS map showed a direct trail to the summit of Cedar Rock.  DO NOT TAKE THIS TRAIL.  At two points, the trail scales a shear rock face for 20-30 yards.  Only rock climbers should go this way.
The better but longer way is to turn right at Butter Gap on the ALT and continue to the unmarked intersection of ALT and an unmarked trail leading to the summit of Cedar Rock.  This is the route I returned on.  Dean ~ K2JB
